1
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:15,080
It- It's out.

2
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:29,039
P-President.

3
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:29,660
Pres...

4
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,140
President.

5
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:32,759
Chen Jiadong

6
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:34,940
has made a move.

7
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:36,300
Quick, tell me.

8
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,360
Okay, I'll speak quickly.

9
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:42,800
Chen Jiadong just went... went...

10
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,200
to...

11
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:45,560
Hurry up.

12
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:47,780
He went to the pier.

13
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:49,080
He bought a ticket

14
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:53,120
for a boat back to Quanzhou tomorrow morning.

15
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:55,360
Bastard.

16
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,759
Gather our men immediately

17
00:01:56,759 --> 00:01:58,360
to intercept him at the pier.

18
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:00,490
We must get the photos back.

19
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,650
Understood.

20
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:02,440
Let's go.

21
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:11,800
Hello,

22
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,780
is this Inspector Luo?

23
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:15,880
Hassan.

24
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,320
Are you sure Chen Jiadong

25
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:19,720
will leave Malaya today?

26
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:21,880
No.

27
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:23,650
He won't?

28
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:26,120
It's impossible for him not to leave.

29
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,840
I saw him buy the boat ticket with my own eyes.

30
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,680
That's why our boss

31
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:32,680
asked me to help you catch him.

32
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:34,000
Our boss said

33
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:36,400
if we catch Chen Jiadong,

34
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,720
we will be heavily rewarded.

35
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:41,820
Where is your boss?

36
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,079
At the city gate.

37
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:48,440
How did he know

38
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:50,640
that Chen Jiadong would pull a

39
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:51,920
bait

40
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,440
and

41
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,280
switch?

42
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,079
Right.

43
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:57,200
He's already guarding there

44
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,920
just to prevent Chen Jiadong

45
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,480
from escaping through the city gate

46
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:02,410
and taking a boat back to Quanzhou.

47
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:04,920
I find that your boss

48
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,340
is a real China expert.

49
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,640
He understands Chinese strategies

50
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:09,720
inside and out.

51
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,160
I think Chen Jiadong

52
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,400
won't be able to escape even if he had wings.

53
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,240
Thanks for your hard work, brother.

54
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:24,700
Freeze!

55
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,100
Where are you from?

56
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,800
We're from Zhicheng Bureau.

57
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,600
Our bureau has a batch of goods

58
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,329
to be shipped to Khmer for sale.

59
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,760
Here is our pass.

60
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,480
Zhicheng Bureau.

61
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,480
Listen up, everyone.

62
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:46,280
The Japanese Chamber of Commerce lost an item.

63
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,480
It's very important.

64
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:49,360
So the superiors ordered that

65
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,620
all people and goods leaving the city...

66
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,000
You must be searched.

67
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:54,880
Chief.

68
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,360
We have a situation.

69
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:07,920
Freeze!

70
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:13,400
Wangshu.

71
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:16,170
It really is you.

72
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,440
What?

73
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,160
You're risking your life

74
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,079
for that Chen Jiadong?

75
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:20,560
Luo Wang,

76
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,760
you Japanese lackey!

77
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,400
Don't speak so harshly,

78
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:23,930
will you?

79
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,280
And don't take advantage of the fact that I like you

80
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:29,610
to ruin my career, okay?

81
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,970
Who cares if you like me?

82
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,520
Get lost, you lackey!

83
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,460
Where is Chen Jiadong?

84
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:41,850
I'm asking you, where is he?

85
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,159
Normally,

86
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,370
you always affectionately

87
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,040
call him

88
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,159
Jiadong.

89
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:47,930
So why now

90
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,720
is he using you as bait

91
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,000
while hiding like a coward?

92
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,060
He's a coward! Bah!

93
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,520
Jiadong would never be like you!

94
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,320
Like me?

95
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,340
Let me tell you,

96
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,060
Chen Jiadong won't escape today.

97
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,200
And he could never be like me!

98
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,240
Alright.

99
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,250
Search the place first!

100
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,240
These are the remittance letters

101
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,440
our agency is sending to Quanzhou.

102
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:13,440
Don't break them.

103
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:15,440
There's nothing you want in there.

104
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,200
These belong to the British.

105
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,280
I order you to open it.

106
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,800
Hurry up if you don't want to die.

107
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:27,020
Open the goods and let them check.

108
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:27,940
Search.

109
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:33,000
Checking even the foreigners' goods.

110
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,840
If the British blame us,

111
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:36,400
someone will definitely

112
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,760
be in deep trouble.

113
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:40,880
Chief.

114
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:43,040
These are the British's goods after all,

115
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,280
and we are on their turf.

116
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:45,920
We can't afford to offend them.

117
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:48,380
Besides, these baskets can't hide a person.

118
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,360
All right.

119
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:50,860
Let them go.

120
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,680
All right, let them go.

121
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,280
Go.

122
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,080
Thanks, brother.

123
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:09,520
You idiot.

124
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,060
Lin Wangshu simply

125
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,160
does not have

126
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,960
the evidence we are looking for.

127
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:16,680
Now,

128
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:18,560
the Chinese Chamber of Commerce

129
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,240
has joined the Malayan authorities

130
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,120
to pressure us.

131
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,320
They demand the release of Lin Wangshu.

132
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,010
The photos must still be

133
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,480
in Chen Jiadong's hands.

134
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,480
Did he not leave Malaya

135
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:30,360
by land?

136
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:31,570
Impossible.

137
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,260
I've been watching the city gate.

138
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,440
He couldn't have escaped

139
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:36,640
right under my nose.

140
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:42,120
Hasan, Rajan.

141
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:42,840
Hurry,

142
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,560
gather the men and follow me.

143
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,080
Yes.

144
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,920
What's wrong, President Yamada?

145
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,320
There's no time to explain,

146
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:51,180
Inspector Luo.

147
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,560
Hurry up, take your men

148
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,360
and follow me.

149
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:56,180
We should still be able to catch up. Let's go.

150
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:57,840
Manager Zhao.

151
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:01,680
Oh no.

152
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,090
They are chasing us.

153
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:04,780
Damn it.

154
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,600
They found us anyway.

155
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:07,760
Manager Zhao,

156
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,120
we are no match for them.

157
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,120
Let's hide first.

158
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,210
Makes sense.

159
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,280
Avoid a head-on clash.

160
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,440
Everyone, hide quickly.

161
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,370
Hurry, let's go.

162
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,140
President Yamada,

163
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,000
how are you so sure

164
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,860
that Chen Jiadong took this road?

165
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:20,490
Just now,

166
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,360
when inspecting at the city gate,

167
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,240
I ran into Zhicheng Agency's

168
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:25,080
courier team.

169
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,600
They said they were heading to Khmer to deliver goods.

170
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:31,040
I know about this.

171
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:32,240
Their pass

172
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,640
was issued by our police station.

173
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,360
But what does it

174
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,490
have to do with this?

175
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,460
To deliver goods to Khmer,

176
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,500
wouldn't the waterway be faster?

177
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,680
Besides, they have their own boats.

178
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:44,080
Why would they take the long way

179
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:45,240
and travel by land?

180
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,040
It's a decoy.

181
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:46,840
I get it.

182
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:47,560
They deliberately

183
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,840
let Lin Wangshu act as bait at the pier

184
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:49,480
to lure us in.

185
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,080
Meanwhile,

186
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,000
they had Chen Jiadong take the land route

187
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:51,930
to leave Malaya.

188
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:52,490
Exactly.

189
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,400
As of now,

190
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,159
this is the only possibility.

191
00:07:55,159 --> 00:07:55,960
Their speed

192
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,000
won't be too fast.

193
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,970
We can definitely catch up to them.

194
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,040
What's wrong?

195
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,250
Something feels wrong.

196
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,640
Jiadong, Mingshu, you go first. I'll cover you.

197
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:36,600
No, Mr. Zhao.

198
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:37,700
We leave together.

199
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,480
Go now.

200
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:40,120
Or none of us can leave.

201
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,049
Don't forget your mission.

202
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,370
Jiadong.

203
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,680
Mr. Zhao is right.

204
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:45,400
Let's go.

205
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:46,560
Go!

206
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,280
Cover!

207
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:53,520
Chen Jiadong!

208
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:54,200
After them!

209
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:06,880
Stop.

210
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:10,760
Stop.

211
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,480
Don't move.

212
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,080
Lin Mingshu.

213
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:22,960
I almost missed

214
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,620
a suspicious person like you.

215
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,000
Leave Chen Jiadong here.

216
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:28,760
Perhaps

217
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,320
I might consider sparing your life.

218
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,360
I still admire you.

219
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:35,680
I won't believe

220
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,480
a despicable Japanese like you.

221
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,840
You are already

222
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:42,920
fish in my net.

223
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,320
Just hand over the photos.

224
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:48,880
Okay.

225
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,420
We can give you the photos,

226
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,800
but you have to show your sincerity

227
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:54,660
and not kill us.

228
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:57,600
Sure.

229
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,330
Bring them here.

230
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,300
The photos are right here.

231
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,240
Here you go.
